summary: A federal appeals court has upheld a law that could ban TikTok from operating in the United States unless the app finds a buyer. The court rejected TikTok's argument that the law was unconstitutional. The government has argued that TikTok, which is owned by a Chinese company, poses a national security threat. TikTok has denied the allegations. If the law is not overturned, TikTok will be banned in the US starting in January 2025. The company has said it is exploring all options to continue operating in the US, including finding a buyer.

name: Dick Van Dyke
summary: Dick Van Dyke, the legendary actor, made a remarkable appearance in Coldplay's music video for "All My Love" shortly before his 99th birthday. Despite his advanced age, Van Dyke showcased his youthful spirit by singing, dancing barefoot, and reflecting on his life. In interviews, Van Dyke expressed his gratitude for the experience and spoke candidly about his mortality, stating that he is not afraid of death and recognizes that his time could come soon. The video has garnered widespread attention, highlighting Van Dyke's enduring talent and positive outlook on life.

His record-smashing campaign saw him dominate the league with his unmatched skills and contributions, leading Inter Miami to new heights. This accolade adds to Messi's long list of honors, solidifying his status as one of the greatest footballers of all time.

summary: Oklahoma State University (OSU) and football coach Mike Gundy have reportedly reached an agreement on a restructured contract. Previous reports had indicated a standoff between Gundy and OSU over his future, with the university reportedly seeking a pay cut after a disappointing 0-9 season in Big 12 play. The new contract's details have not been officially announced, but it appears that Gundy will remain the head coach of the Cowboys.
